# Plan: Add FMP MCP Server

## Context
Financial Modeling Prep (FMP) provides a cloud-hosted MCP server accessible via SSE transport.
The user has a magic setup link that embeds their API key directly in the URL.
Currently, `~/.claude/settings.json` has no `mcpServers` section.

## Change

**File:** `C:\Users\CaveUser\.claude\settings.json`

Add a `mcpServers` block with the FMP entry using SSE transport:

```json
"mcpServers": {
  "fmp": {
    "type": "sse",
    "url": "https://financialmodelingprep.com/mcp?apikey=d56Yr3SRjO1THp2GU8dI3csmj88sw2QK"
  }
}
```

The full updated file will be:

```json
{
  "enabledPlugins": { ... },
  "extraKnownMarketplaces": { ... },
  "autoUpdatesChannel": "latest",
  "mcpServers": {
    "fmp": {
      "type": "sse",
      "url": "https://financialmodelingprep.com/mcp?apikey=d56Yr3SRjO1THp2GU8dI3csmj88sw2QK"
    }
  }
}
```

## Verification
After saving, restart Claude Code. Run `/mcp` or check the MCP server list â€” `fmp` should appear as connected.
If SSE transport is not supported in this Claude Code version, fallback is `"type": "http"` with the same URL.

